Your project confirms the `TestContext.TestName` issue at **line 13** of `SetupTests.cs`. In v4, `TestName` is unavailable during `[ClassInitialize]` because no specific test is running yet.

**Fix** — move the `TestName` access to `[TestInitialize]`:

```csharp
[ClassInitialize]
public static void ClassInit(TestContext context)
{
    // Class-level setup only (no per-test properties)
}

[TestInitialize]
public void TestInit()
{
    var testName = TestContext.TestName;
    // Log setup for specific test
}
```

Otherwise your project looks clean — target framework is `net8.0` ✅, using `MSTest 4.1.0` ✅, no deprecated APIs in use. Want me to apply the fix?
